                    "name": "Activate",
                    "ability_type": "offensive",
                    "action_type": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "action_type",
                        "name": "Two Actions"
                    },
                    "frequency": "once per day",
                    "effect": "The smog created by the  *smogger* thickens into a toxic element that burns the eyes, blisters flesh, and causes fits of coughing. All creatures in the smog cloud, including you, must attempt a DC 32 Fortitude save\u2014creatures that must breathe and aren't holding their breath take a \u20132 circumstance penalty to this save.",
                    "requirement": "The  *smogger's* above activation is in effect",
                    "critical_success": "The creature is unaffected.",
                    "success": "The creature is sickened 1.",
                    "failure": "The creature is sickened 1 (or increases their sickened condition value to 2 if it isn't holding its breath). The creature also takes 4d6 poison damage.",
                    "critical_failure": "As failure, but the creature takes 8d6 poison damage.",
